+-----------------------------------------------------------------------
| Running ${PKGSTEM} on OpenBSD
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------

Startup
=======
LXQt desktop environment is launched through the 'startlxqtwayland' script.
It can be run from a VT if the permissions are correctly set on the various
DRM devices required by wayland, which should be the default.

An lxqt-wayland.desktop file is provided for use by greetd.
